t class=m><span class=title> Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> Recently I spent some time in OT doing Outpost faction work hoping to finally be able to port myself back to a vendor that liked me as opposed to selling to indifferent merchants.  Then a couple of friends sent me a tell asking me if I wanted to join them in HS, of course my greedy little mind thought nothing but, &quot;Nice I'm gonna be an erudite!!!&quot;, and I joined them.  After three days of camping nothing but the entrance, and a couple of short ventures into the available wings (we didn't have a full group so we stuck there) I finally looked at my faction messages and realized that the VS faction I had been working on couldn't get any worse, DOH!  Now with the new changes to the &quot;secret handshake&quot; you can only trade while sneaking, not hiding, and of course right accross from the skelly I have to hand the sarnak warbraids to, there are 5 or so blue con skellies that'll hand me my head on a silver platter by the time I hit trade.<br><br>So my question is, does the red wine quest in Neriak raise VS faction for the outpost?  If so will I be able to do it while sneaking?  Also the OT hammer is 2HB (a skill we don't have) but all/all, can anyone confirm with any certainty whether or not I can weild this crazy thing?<br><br>Meff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubearberry.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bearberry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 10:54:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Now with the new changes to the &quot;secret handshake&quot; you can only trade while sneaking, not hiding<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>You could never trade while hiding.  You became visible when you opened the trade window.  The only difference now is you have to click Hide off manually instead of having it come off by itself.<br><br>EDIT:<br>The red wine quest does not raise VS faction.  The only ways I know of are to do the warbraid quest, or kill dragons in VP.  And rogues can wield the hammer even with no 2HB skill. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubearberry.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bearberry</A> at: 5/17/02 10:56:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufilobeto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filobeto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 10:57:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> One lil click of the mask of deception took me from Scowling to Ami / App (one of those)  - no handshake required <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uandrewbb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AndrewBB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 11:03:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> Exp and fun in HS &gt; OT faction.<br><br>Although it's not a bad idea to check out faction messages, just in case, and ask about the lore of the place.<br><br>In this case you ran some errands for the outpost, they figure 'hey this guy may be okay'... but then you ran into the tomb of the boss man's beloved and desecrated it... ya gotta figure at that point you just missed the memo that said 'yer fired'.<br><br>I've not known anyone to be able to get their faction back up once they've hit max KOS, sorry. But on the bright side you can hunt in HS without worrying about faction now. Honestly, with Luclin, it's not as big a benefit as it once was. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usithen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sithen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 11:17:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> Oh well, I'm not too worried about it, it's one less thing on my list of things I have to do with this character, more grinding time instead.  By the way, one little click on my mask of deception, and I'm still scowling ready to attack, Illusions only fix racial hatreds, not diety hatreds or bad faction, that's why I stayed out of Crushbone way back in the day.  Boy am I glad I've already gotten my notes for both my Epic and my Mask of the Coercer, now never have to go to Neriak again.<br><br>Meff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhandorphist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HandorPhist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 11:48:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> There is a way to improve your OT faction, but it's a major pain and at this point will take some serious time.<br><br>First, collect as many warbraids as you can.  Then round up a monk and non-KOS friend (can be the same person).  Have the monk pull the captain out of the fort and FD.  Then have your non-KOS friend hail the captain.  You sneak up behind and turn in 4 warbraids at a time.<br><br>This works well for folks that are threatening -- but if you're bottomed-out KOS that's a whole ton of warbraids. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ustixum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stixum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 12:09:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> One trick you can use is have a friend hail the Capt turning him away from the marines while your behind the marines, keep sneak on and hand the stuff into him that way.  You should be able to target and hand him stuff without a problem that way, might try fooling around with f9 and try handing him the stuff that way while still sneaking behind the marines (still using a friend to hail him).<br><br>It's a pain to do, but it should work if your that die hard to get your OT faction up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usithen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sithen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 12:59:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the advice all, I might just try one of these options out, but I won't be doing it for a while, maybe I'll come back in 6 or so levels and assassinate the stupid Sarnaks.  Then again, maybe I should head to Nurga/Droga and become a friend of the sarnaks, it'll be about the same amount of work for much better rewards, gotta get that halfling mask first though...<br><br>Meff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufinneus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Finneus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 2:09:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> We can weild it, but we suck at using it so we tend to stand around swinging for a while before it goes off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unortherner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 3:13:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like I wasted a lot of time in OT...</span><hr size=1> I don't know about that Finneus, it always seems to proc for me pretty well.  Heck, riposte disc + gate hammer will more often than not get you out of pretty amusing trains.  (Presuming you want to end up in the outpost of course.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhiwinhulose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HiwinHulose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/18/02 3:32:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Triggered Faydedar gives positive VS faction</span><hr size=1> The triggered Faydedar encounter for the druid epic also gives a positive VS faction boost, although for the life of me I don't know why..<br><br>Hiwin Hulose<br>56 Halfling Blackguard<br>Recently voted 83rd best rogue on TP top 50 rogue list <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uragnarita.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ragnarita</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/18/02 8:02:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><