ttp://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udavooddaehmon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Davood Daehmon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/19/02 5:05:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmmmm</span><hr size=1> Actually puppet strings ARE from pof. <br><br>they used to drop off Cazic.. they drop off one of the  golems now <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/19/02 6:48:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> confirm</span><hr size=1> Yah, PoF drop from fear/dread/terror now, nothing to do with PoM.  10 charges of the level 49 enchanter charm if memory serves (got a set in my inventory, don't remember for absolutely sure which charm it is tho), instant cast.<br><br>Pretty rare tho, those mini's have a fairly big loot table to pick from.<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usilvermouse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvermouse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/19/02 10:01:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> I'm sure the hammer ports you within kos distance to skeletons in OT. Are they green to 60? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umilenah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milenah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/20/02 2:24:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> I saw a warrior friend of mine use the hammer to port himself to OT... he ended up on the boat, safely away from the skellies. Not sure if you consistently end up there though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usendailia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sendailia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/20/02 8:41:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> You end up under the deck the north boat right next to a skeleton worker.  There is a &quot;hatch&quot; you can see leading above deck but you can't get through it.  You need to just run up the side of hte boat and you'll pass right through the decking.  <br><br>At 60 my rog has enough time to hide/sneak before it aggros (which it will fairly quickly).  There is also a wondering dragoon that goes near the boat who loves to pick up aggro from the skeleton and kill any intruders.  <br><br>Which btw if you are a FD class, remember to /q out.  The dragoon doesn't have a &quot;home&quot; so aggro never resets. As my poor SK has found out many a time...even after 5+ min FD.<br><br>You can run to skyfire zone fairly easily training the dragoon and cliff golems behind if you just want to make a run for it.  Just remember to have SoW or do some creative JBoot running. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umarikavonmordo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marika Von Mordo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/20/02 10:20:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure I would say exp/fun in HS &gt; OT faction.  I find the hammer to be invaluable as means of getting out of dungeons if I have to leave a raid early (and there is no wizard) or even if I just want to get quickly from some back water in Luclin or Velious back onto Kunark.<br><br>I have however hunted HS extensively so the zone is kind of a been there/done that thing for me.<br><br>As far as killing VP dragons raising OT faction they certainly give faction messages but I have yet to raise a faction level (from warmly to ally) after 3 VP clearings.  So they either don't raise it that much or do not raise it beyond a certain level.<br><br>Marika <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umarikavonmordo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marika Von Mordo</A> at: 5/20/02 10:21:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span cl